        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Experimental boundary conditions replicated within ±5% — Gradation 2",
        "description": "Flow rate and rotational speed set points in CFD match bench test within ±5%. Blood analog viscosity uncertainty is ±8%; this wider bound is disclosed with rationale that glycerol-water mixture viscosity varies with temperature."
      },
      "rationale": "Flow rate and RPM boundary conditions are replicated within ±2% of bench test set points. Blood analog (glycerol-water) viscosity was measured at 22°C ± 1°C, introducing ±8% viscosity uncertainty that propagates to approximately ±12% uncertainty in hemolysis index. This is explicitly disclosed in the UQ record. Confidence in full test-condition equivalence is approximately 50%; the limitation is documented and accepted as residual uncertainty at MRL 2."
    },
    {
