        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI directly maps to clinical hemolysis endpoint — Gradation 2",
        "description": "Hemolysis index (HI) and relative hemolysis index (RH) are established surrogates for plasma-free hemoglobin. Relevance confidence ~50% due to power-law model uncertainty in the Giersiepen-Wurzinger damage model."
      },
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is the accepted surrogate for RBC damage in CFD; however, its empirical coefficients carry ±50% uncertainty as documented in published literature. This uncertainty propagates directly to the QoI. The limitation is honestly disclosed: the model is adequate for rank-ordering operating conditions (the COU decision) even if absolute HI predictions are uncertain. Achieved level 2 is justified for the rank-ordering decision context."
    },
